The paper deals with image classification and search using coding approaches, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also evaluates the performance of different methods on image retrieval and fine-grained classification benchmarks, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes and evaluates alternative choices for patch extraction, which involves image processing techniques and could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
